<br>
Ok, so the game is way different beyond 35. That is fine, EQ was really never designed for PvP/Duels in the first place. Listen, when you have a game where the offensive powers of the clasess go up exponentially, but the defensive powers do not then you have a game that is completely unbalanced for PVP. <br>
<br>
One shot (dd's) = Death<br>
2 Shot Bow hits = Death<br>
One shot DOT/ Run away = Death<br>
<br>
These abilities were made for slaughtering mobs that have 30k hp, huge AC and MAD resists. Not for a mage, wizard, enchanter, druid, shaman, bard, warrior, rogue, cleric, monk, beastmaster to take.<br>
<br>
I guess I shouldn't even joined in this discussion because all of my tactics and theories are based from the level range that is somewhat PvP friendly. On the PvP servers, level 20-40 are PRIME. You can not beat these levels, they are the funnest for PvP bar non. <br>
<br>
Please go ahead and take back any of my posts within this thread. No need to have to come back and slam any of my 'newbie' spam.<br>
<br>
